&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We&#39;re not currently hiring for overseas nurses - must have NMC Registration.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mary Ward – South Warwickshire NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mary Ward is a 22 bedded Ward that cares for Respiratory patients with acute and chronic respiratory illness and disease.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mary Ward nursing staff are trained to care for patients with a range of Respiratory conditions including those with COPD, Cancer or Respiratory Failure. Some of our patients have the need for chest drains, tracheostomies or need non-invasive ventilation, CPAP or high flow oxygen therapies. We adapted well to COVID 19 and changed our working practices accordingly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We work closely with Critical Care Outreach and ITU to ensure that the patient has the most appropriate care, in the best environment with the skilled team they need. On Mary we have a supportive team of Consultants and Senior Nurses who work closely with the patients, their family and the Junior staff to ensure that a holistic assessment of the patient&#39;s need is achieved.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We care for patients from diagnosis, throughout regular admissions until in some cases the end of their life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We work well with the palliative care teams both in the hospital, local Hospices and the community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mary Ward’s manager Sara has a keen interest in staff development, is an experienced mentor and preceptor with an extensive background in both Acute and Palliative care. Therefore she is in a great position to advise staff on their personal development plans.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All working patterns considered (including night, and weekend contracts) please contact us to tell us what you are looking for.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What are we looking for?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Nurses who want high dependency / Emergency Care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Newly qualified nurses who are looking for a supportive environment to shape their nursing career.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced nurses that are looking for a new challenge in respiratory nursing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Candidates who are interested in helping us become a flagship ward for palliative and end of life care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What can we offer?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our manager Sara is determined to help all staff achieve their goals and ambitions and can offer a personalised plan for staff to ensure their potential is reached, including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Development pathways to specialist or managerial roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Four Week Induction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learning and Training Opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A range of clinical skills training to suit the individual as well as the ward.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentorship and preceptor support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Link nurse roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Roster patterns to support a healthy work/life balance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clearly structured career pathway.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We are launching a 6 Bed Non Invasive Ventilation Unit where our Nurses will be working closely with the outreach team to take patients from A&amp;E and ITU.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What does the trust offer?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Staff Benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lease Car Scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Electronics Scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Childcare vouchers and nursery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Multiple car parking sites&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health and well-being services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clearly defined support network from ward buddy system right up to Head of Nursing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
